      "beast_baseline": "Hey, I'm running a linear regression on some housing price data but I've hit a snag with the residuals. They don't look normally distributed at all—there's some heavy skew and the tails are looking pretty weird. What are my best options for handling this so I don't mess up my inferences?",
      "beast_suffix": "",
