    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Since your residuals are not normally distributed, you can try transforming your dependent variable, like using a log transformation on the housing prices. Alternatively, robust regression methods can be employed, which are less sensitive to violations of normality and outliers in the residuals. If the issue persists, consider using non-parametric methods or examining if certain features need to be modeled differently. These approaches can help ensure your inference remains relatively sound despite the data's distributional quirks.",
