      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Pruning outliers is risky unless you are absolutely certain they are data entry errors, as they might represent genuine, albeit rare, phenomena. You can start by visualizing them using Cook's distance or leverage plots to see if they are influential points affecting your regression line. If they are genuine, consider winsorizing them by capping the extreme values rather than outright deletion. This acknowledges their existence while mitigating their disproportionate impact on the model.",
      "source": "target",
