      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A quicker heuristic is to look at standardized residuals exceeding $\\pm 3$, as this flags points outside three standard deviations from the regression line. For a broader view, you can examine the leverage of each point; high leverage points suggest the feature values themselves are unusual, which is often a problem. If a point has both high standardized residuals AND high leverage, it's a prime candidate for being a truly problematic outlier. This combination gives you a good, rapid flag.",
      "source": "target",
